This repository is shared publicly so that authorized individuals — primarily
the Taste agency ambassador / power-user cohort, plus any other persons
authorized in writing by the copyright holder — can install the Pack on their
machines and use it as their daily Claude Code configuration, including for
work performed in the course of their employment or engagement.

You may:
  - View the source code in this repository.
  - Clone the repository to install the Pack on machines you use for
    authorized work.
  - Use the Pack as your daily Claude Code configuration on those machines —
    including on client projects, internal projects, and personal projects.
    The Pack is a working tool. Using it on the work you are paid to do is
    explicitly permitted.
  - Modify your local copy to fit your workflow. Add your own rules, skills,
    hooks, and templates. The Pack is a starting point, not a frozen artifact.
  - Re-clone or pull updates from this repository to refresh your installation.

You may NOT, without prior written permission from the copyright holder:
  - Redistribute, republish, mirror, rehost, or otherwise share this
    repository or any part of it outside the authorized audience. The "fork"
    button on GitHub remains technically functional — that is a platform
    limitation, not a permission.
  - Use the Pack as the basis for a derivative work that you publish, sell,
    sublicense, or otherwise make available to third parties.
  - Package the Pack, or a recognisable derivative of it, into a commercial
    product or service offering of your own.
  - Use the source code or contents for training machine learning models.

The intent of this license: people who are authorized to use the Pack can use
it freely as a working tool. People who want to take the Pack and turn it into
their own thing — fork it publicly, sell it, repackage it under another name —
cannot, without asking first.

Unauthorized redistribution will be enforced via GitHub's DMCA process.

